This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories, as it deals with 3D object detection in the context of autonomous driving. The use of a convolutional neural net (CNN) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents results on the KITTI benchmark, which is a popular dataset for computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CVPR) research.
